text: Latifur Rahman (28 August 1945 – 1 July 2020) was a Bangladeshi businessman. From 2014 to 2017, he was a member of the International Chamber of Commerce. He was the chairman of Transcom Group. Rahman died from an illness at his home in the Comilla District, Bangladesh at the age of 74.ট্রান্সকম গ্রুপের চেয়ারম্যান লতিফুর রহমান মারা গেছেন ==References== ==Other websites== * * Category:1945 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Bangladeshi businesspeople Category:People from Chittagong Division
